{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1f32dc08-c05a-4df7-b908-dd3507919b4f","content":"`SafeAreaEdges` isn't the right property here. You likely need a combination of these:\n\n**1. Hide the nav bar** (if using Shell or NavigationPage):\n```xml\nShell.NavBarIsVisible=\"False\"\n<!-- or -->\nNavigationPage.HasNavigationBar=\"False\"\n```\n\n**2. Disable iOS safe area insets** on the page:\n```xml\nxmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\nios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\"\n```\n\n**3. Android edge-to-edge** — on .NET 10 / Android 15+, edge-to-edge is enforced by default, but on older APIs you may need to opt in from your `MainActivity`:\n```csharp\nWindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window, false);\n```\n\n**4. Fill the image properly:**\n```xml\n<Image Source=\"photo.jpg\"\n       Aspect=\"AspectFill\"\n       HorizontalOptions=\"Fill\"\n       VerticalOptions=\"Fill\" />\n```\n\n**Minimal full example:**\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\"\n             Shell.NavBarIsVisible=\"False\"\n             x:Class=\"MyApp.PhotoViewerPage\">\n    <Image Source=\"photo.jpg\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe most common culprit is the navigation bar still being visible — start there.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1ca07d54-472b-437a-aa39-2f80f83ac942","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is working on a .NET MAUI app targeting .NET 10 and wants an image to go edge-to-edge, behind the status bar and navigation bar. They've set `SafeAreaEdges=\"None\"` on the ContentPage but still see padding.\n\nThis is a common .NET MAUI question. Let me think about what's needed:\n\n1. **`IgnoreSafeArea`** - In .NET MAUI, setting `SafeAreaEdges=\"None\"` on the page might not be enough. The key property is typically on the view itself or involves platform-specific configuration.\n\n2. For true edge-to-edge on .NET MAUI / .NET 10:\n   - On **iOS**, I need to use `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\"` to allow content behind the status bar and notch areas.\n   - On **Android**, edge-to-edge behavior depends on the Android version and MAUI version, but I may need platform-specific code to handle system bar insets properly.\n\nThe user is likely also missing the navigation bar hiding step—if the page is wrapped in a `NavigationPage` or `Shell`, that bar takes up space and needs to be explicitly hidden. I should also make sure the image itself has `Aspect=\"AspectFill\"` to properly fill the screen. Let me clarify that `SafeAreaEdges` isn't a standard MAUI property, so the real solution involves the platform-specific iOS setting and potentially hiding the navigation bar.","outputTokens":1249},"id":"e31da5b7-76db-4056-a109-572216c19190","timestamp":"2026-04-09T15:28:06.391Z","parentId":"353f97b0-773a-4a0a-85d0-3d0c42022203"}
